<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-51-0481 </DOCNO><TEXT>The danger of world-wide climatic changes brought about by man as a resultof energy consumption, growth of population, clearfelling of forests,fertilization etc. has increasingly become also the object of publicdiscussions in recent years. The paper sums up the most important processesliable to entail global changes of climate. New scientific results arepointed out, especially statistical studies based on observations ofclimate, to verify experiments using climatic models. This is followedby a catalogue of preventive steps deemed necessary.</TEXT></DOC>